  "text": "In medical education, feedback for GPiTs could be provided by GPtrainers as well as fellow GPiTs. In the latter case, one speaks of peer feedback. [CITATION_1] defines giving and receiving peer feedback as an ''arrangement in which individuals consider the mount, level, value, worth, quality or success of the products or outcomes of learning of peers of similar status'' (p. 250). During peer feedback, participants are observed by their peers while they are performing. The level of proficiency demonstrated is analysed and reported on and is then compared with predetermined performance standards. All participants have the opportunity to attain the standards, and can thus play a role in giving constructive feedback to their peers.",
